wiki.content: "GOLDWING" is a song by Billie Eilish, recorded for her second studio album Happier Than Ever. It was written by Eilish and her brother Finneas O'Connell, who also produced it. The song was released through Darkroom and Interscope Records on July 30th, 2021 with the other tracks from the album. The intro of the song, wasn't originally written by FINNEAS and Billie Eilish, it was originally written by Gustav Holst ("Choral Hymns from de Rig Veda, 3rd Group, Op.26: No. 3. Hymn to Vena" // Minute 2:48). The idea of including this part of Gustav's song, was brought to Billie since she sang in a Chore when she was young. This one of the songs that Billie used to sing with her Chore. In this video, we can see her singing this exact same song with her choir when she was young (Girl with Lavander colred hair) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mCVYri1Zzjs&ab_channel=eilishedits Read more on Last.fm.
